<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="733" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Emperor of Korea</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-16"><hi rend="italic">September 16,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I regret exceedingly your excellency’s recent carriage accident, and
                            heartily congratulate you on your happy escape. I trust you will
                            speedily recover from the effects of the collision.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hiung</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Emperor
                                    Daicher of Daihan.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>